trans-unit.source: Represents the name of a version of the .NET Framework.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName"></xref> class from a string that contains information about a version of the .NET Framework.
The <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.%23ctor%28System.String%29> constructor parses a string in the following format.
*identifier*, Version=*versionNumber*[, Profile=*profileName*]
Components in square brackets are optional.
The following table describes each component.
Component
Description
*identifier*
An arbitrary string that identifies this <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName> instance.
*versionNumber*

A string that represents the version of the .NET Framework, in the form [v]*major*.*minor*[.*build*.*revision*], where "v" can be either uppercase or lowercase, and the brackets denote optional elements of a version number.
*profileName*
An arbitrary string that represents the profile of the .NET Framework version.
Typically, it is used to denote some subset of the .NET Framework, such as the .NET Compact Framework or Silverlight.
If both *versionNumber* and *profileName* are present, they can appear in any order after *identifier*.
These strings are defined by the "Version" and "Profile" keywords, which are not case-sensitive.
The values of the *identifier*, *versionNumber*, and *profileName* components define the values of this <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName> object's properties as follows:
Any leading or trailing white space in the *identifier* component is removed and the resulting string is assigned to the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.Identifier%2A> property.
Any leading or trailing white space and the initial "v" or "V", if present, are removed from the `versionNumber`.

The returned string is then passed to the <xref:System.Version.%23ctor%28System.String%29?displayProperty=fullName> constructor, and the resulting <xref:System.Version?displayProperty=fullName> object is assigned to the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.Version%2A> property.
Any leading or trailing white space in the `profileName` component is removed and the resulting string is assigned to the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.Profile%2A> property.
The following are examples of valid strings that can be passed to the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.%23ctor%2A> constructor:
.NET Framework, Version=4.0
.NETFramework, Version=4.0
.NET Framework, Version=2.0, Profile=Compact
.NET Framework, Version=v4.0, Profile=Compact
.NET Framework, Profile=Full, Version=2.0.0
A string that contains .NET Framework version information.
frameworkName is .
-or-
frameworkName has fewer than two components or more than three components.
-or-
frameworkName does not include a major and minor version number.
-or-
frameworkName does not include a valid version number.
frameworkName is `null`.

Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName"></xref> class from a string and a <xref href="System.Version"></xref> object that identify a .NET Framework version.
The <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName> class requires that a <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.Version%2A> object include at least a major and minor version number.
A string that identifies a .NET Framework version.
An object that contains .NET Framework version information.
identifier is .
identifier is `null`.
-or-
version is `null`.

Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName"></xref> class from a string, a <xref href="System.Version"></xref> object that identifies a .NET Framework version, and a profile name.
The <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName> class requires that a <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.Version%2A> object include at least a major and minor version number.
A string that identifies a .NET Framework version.
An object that contains .NET Framework version information.
A profile name.
identifier is .
identifier is `null`.
-or-
version is `null`.
Returns a value that indicates whether this <xref href="System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName"></xref> instance represents the same .NET Framework version as a specified object.

The method converts `obj` to a <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName> object and calls the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.Equals%28System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName%29?displayProperty=fullName> overload to test for equality.
If the conversion does not succeed or if `obj` is `null`, the method returns `false`.
The object to compare to the current instance.
`true` if every component of the current object matches the corresponding component of obj; otherwise, `false`.

Returns a value that indicates whether this <xref href="System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName"></xref> instance represents the same .NET Framework version as a specified <xref href="System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName"></xref> instance.
The method tests for equality by returning the result of the following comparisons:
An ordinal comparison of the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.Identifier%2A> property values of the current instance and `other`.
An ordinal comparison of the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.Profile%2A> property values of the current instance and `other`.
A comparison of the version properties by calling the <xref:System.Version.Equals%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method.
The object to compare to the current instance.
`true` if every component of the current object matches the corresponding component of other; otherwise, `false`.
Gets the full name of this <xref href="System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName"></xref> object.
The string returned by the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.FullName%2A> property has the following format:
*identifier*, Version=*version*[, Profile=*profile*]

where *identifier* corresponds to the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.Identifier%2A> property, `version` is equivalent to calling <xref:System.Version.ToString%2A?displayProperty=fullName> on the value of the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.Version%2A> property, and `profile` corresponds to the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.Profile%2A> property.
If a profile has not been assigned to the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName> object, the profile component is not included in the string.
The value of the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.FullName%2A> property is identical to the string returned by the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.ToString%2A> method.
The full name of this <xref href="System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName"></xref> object.
Returns the hash code for the <xref href="System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName"></xref> object.
A 32-bit signed integer that represents the hash code of this instance.
Gets the identifier of this <xref href="System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName"></xref> object.
The value of the read-only <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.Identifier%2A> property is set in the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.%23ctor%2A> class constructor.
The identifier of this <xref href="System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName"></xref> object.
Returns a value that indicates whether two <xref href="System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName"></xref> objects represent the same .NET Framework version.
The <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.op_Equality%2A> method defines the operation of the equality operator for <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName> objects.
Languages that do not support custom operators can call the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.Equals%28System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName%29?displayProperty=fullName> method instead.
The first object to compare.
The second object to compare.
`true` if the left and right parameters represent the same .NET Framework version; otherwise, `false`.
Returns a value that indicates whether two <xref href="System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName"></xref> objects represent different .NET Framework versions.
The <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.op_Inequality%2A> method defines the operation of the inequality operator for <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName> objects.

Languages that do not support custom operators can test for inequality by calling the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.Equals%28System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName%29?displayProperty=fullName> method and reversing its value.
The first object to compare.
The second object to compare.
`true` if the left and right parameters represent different .NET Framework versions; otherwise, `false`.
Gets the profile name of this <xref href="System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName"></xref> object.
The value of the read-only <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.Profile%2A> property is set in the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.%23ctor%2A> class constructor.
The profile name of this <xref href="System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName"></xref> object.
Returns the string representation of this <xref href="System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName"></xref> object.
The string returned by the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.ToString%2A> method has the following format:
*identifier*, Version=*version*[, Profile=*profile*]

where *identifier* corresponds to the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.Identifier%2A> property, `version` is equivalent to calling <xref:System.Version.ToString%2A?displayProperty=fullName> on the value of the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.Version%2A> property, and `profile` corresponds to the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.Profile%2A> property.
If a profile has not been assigned to the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName> object, the profile component is not included in the returned string.
The value returned by the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.ToString%2A> method is identical to the value of the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.FullName%2A> property.
A string that represents this <xref href="System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName"></xref> object.
Gets the version of this <xref href="System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName"></xref> object.
The value of the read-only <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.Version%2A> property is set in the <xref:System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName.%23ctor%2A> class constructor.
An object that contains version information about this <xref href="System.Runtime.Versioning.FrameworkName"></xref> object.
